column12: RNHANES computes the 50th percentile for cycle 1999-2000 to be 0.28, while the summary table reports it as a non-detect.
For 99-00, quantiles come back as detects even though they are NDs because the quantile value is equal to the LOD.
RNHANES computes the 75th at 0.0473, while the summary table puts it at 0.05. This causes RNHANES to classify it as <LOD (the LOD is 0.48), while the summary tables don't.

75th and 90th percentiles for total (no subsetting) are right on the line of being a non-detect -- RNHANES classifies them as non detects, the summary table reports that as being right at the LOD. E.g. RNHANES computes the 75th to be 0.0071, when the summary table reports t at 0.01, so RNHANES is off by 0.0029.

The appendix in the summary table lists the 01-02 LOD as 0.34, but the footnote in the summary table lists it at 0.034. If it is set at 0.34, then the RNHANES values don't match those in the summary table.
